## Introduction to the Turing-Roche Strategic Partnership

Our strategic partnership was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](http://elink.turing.ac._X2NsZGVlPWRtaGxiR3h2YmtCMGRYSnBibWN1WVdNdWRXcyUzZCZyZWNpcGllbnRpZD1jb250YWN0LTQ4ODBhOGMzOTIzY2VjMTE4YzYyMDAyMjQ4NDM0ZmViLWRlMTE1Y2U1Y2M4ODQ0NjNhYzYxNzg1YjNmOTg5ZWRmJmVzaWQ9ZDcwMGVkNDMtMTY3Mi1lYzExLTg5NDMtMDAyMjQ4MDcwNjNlIn0/9XnA4kLju7479nzGOiglRg) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment.

The 'North Star' of our five year partnership is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care.**

We are just at the start of our journey but will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building a strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

You can find more info about our current projects [here](http://elink.turing.ac.).

### Funding Call: Structured Missingness

**Deadline 31st January 2022**

We recently held a series of workshops on the topic of structured missingness with the aim of convening a community of researchers interested in developing new tools and methods around heterogenous data with structured patterns of missing readings. You can read more about the workshops in this report [here](http://elink.turing.ac.).

Following on from the workshops we have now launched a funding call for projects on structured missingness. More info [here](http://elink.turing.ac.).

We are also holding a Q&A session on the funding call on the **12th January at 11am GMT. **You can register for the session [here](http://elink.turing.ac._X2NsZGVlPWRtaGxiR3h2YmtCMGRYSnBibWN1WVdNdWRXcyUzZCZyZWNpcGllbnRpZD1jb250YWN0LTQ4ODBhOGMzOTIzY2VjMTE4YzYyMDAyMjQ4NDM0ZmViLWRlMTE1Y2U1Y2M4ODQ0NjNhYzYxNzg1YjNmOTg5ZWRmJmVzaWQ9ZDcwMGVkNDMtMTY3Mi1lYzExLTg5NDMtMDAyMjQ4MDcwNjNlIn0/4oYhRnSeQaqXJduW3hAoAw).


### Jobs: Senior Research Associate 

**Deadline 1st February 2022**

We are hiring for 2 Senior Research Associates for the Turing-Roche partnership. The posts are full-time for 3 years and will give the post holder(s) experience working closely with both Turing and Roche to help shape direction of the partnership, as well as the freedom to develop their own area of aligned research under mentorship from senior leaders in both academia and industry.

More info at the job ad [here](http://elink.turing.ac.-CdbSF4E7Oqg)- please share widely!


## Current Opportunities at The Alan Turing Institute and Roche

 ![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/group_study_working__0.jpg) 


### Roche Biostatistics Summer Internship for PhD Students

**Deadline 16th January 2022**

This programme gives PhD students in the area of statistics, data science or epidemiology the opportunity to work at Roche for 10 weeks under the supervision of experienced biostatisticians/data scientists and receive a competitive salary. Interns will work on theoretical or applied problems with direct relevance to Roche's ongoing clinical drug-development in areas such as oncology, immunology, infectious disease, ophthalmology, or neuroscience. More info and how to apply [here](http://elink.turing.ac._-roaTB9fZoLytDxvfBw).

### AI UK

The Turing Institute will be holding its flagship two-day AI conference on 22nd-23rd March 2022- exploring themes around the National AI strategy and topical sessions on trends in data science and AI.

The conference currently has an open call for content closing on the **16th January 2022**. Find out more and how to submit a proposal for the conference [here](http://elink.turing.ac._X2NsZGVlPWRtaGxiR3h2YmtCMGRYSnBibWN1WVdNdWRXcyUzZCZyZWNpcGllbnRpZD1jb250YWN0LTQ4ODBhOGMzOTIzY2VjMTE4YzYyMDAyMjQ4NDM0ZmViLWRlMTE1Y2U1Y2M4ODQ0NjNhYzYxNzg1YjNmOTg5ZWRmJmVzaWQ9ZDcwMGVkNDMtMTY3Mi1lYzExLTg5NDMtMDAyMjQ4MDcwNjNlIn0/NQLk8gVTFy3hZbwPjOWRiA).
